raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "py2app" %}
{% set version = "0.28.2" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1c8baf1464a42894fd48435bb1111bb549c077f11aa1180736f5539e22585a70
  patches:
    - distutils.patch  # [python_impl == 'pypy']

build:
  skip: true  # [not osx]
  number: 0
  entry_points:
    - py2applet = py2app.script_py2applet:main
  missing_dso_whitelist:
    - '*/libgcc_s.1.dylib'

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - altgraph >=0.16
    - macholib >=1.16
    - modulegraph >=0.17
    - pip
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - altgraph >=0.16
    - macholib >=1.16
    - modulegraph >=0.17
    - python
    - setuptools

test:
  imports:
    - py2app
    - py2app.apptemplate
    - py2app.bootstrap
    - py2app.bundletemplate
    - py2app.converters
    - py2app.recipes
    - py2app.recipes.PIL
  commands:
    - py2applet

about:
  home: https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/py2app
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: |
    py2app is a Python setuptools command which will allow you to make
    standalone Mac OS X application bundles and plugins from Python scripts.
    py2app is similar in purpose and design to py2exe for Windows.
    py2app must be used on OSX to build applications, it cannot create Mac
    applications on other platforms.
  doc_url: https://py2app.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
  dev_url: https://github.com/ronaldoussoren/py2app

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bkpoon
